{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":2998104,"name":"Griffin Drinkwater","username":"Monarch49","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/9d8465/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-01-25T21:23:53.026Z","cooked":"<p>We are testing the PID for our two Falcon 500 motors which operate our flywheel system. ATM I have just P following the Zeigler-Nichols tuning method. Anyway, the PID is braking our motors and it seems to bad for them considering the horrible screeching sound. Currently our motors are in coast mode so I am not really sure where to go from here.<br>
This is the relevant subsystem:<br>
